Current status of lung transplantation.
 Techniques and indications for single and bilateral lung transplantation have evolved significantly in the past several years.
 Lung transplantation has entered a new era in which transplantation can be achieved with the same degree of success as that achieved with other major organ transplants.
 Many problems, common to organ transplantation remain to be solved including availability of suitable donor organs, improved immunosuppressive regimens, and the ability to properly diagnose and effectively treat organ rejection.
